question:
Which type of locality does the loop in the following C program demonstrate?
```c
float A[N];
float sum = 0.0;
for (int i = 0; i < N; ++i) {
  sum += A[i] + A[i + 1];
}
```
A. Just temporal locality.
B. Just spatial locality.
C. Both temporal and spatial locality.
D. Neither; there is no locality in this loop.
